cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO 

Reasoning: The paper deals with computer vision and graphics, specifically with the problem of extracting 3D parts from single images without part annotations. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves 3D graphics representations and learning, which suggests the categories cs.GR (Computer Graphics), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as likely sub-categories. Finally, the use of a neural network to extract parts and the focus on articulated bodies suggests the category cs.RO (Robotics) as a possible sub-category.
